            <h3>Hormonal Acne</h3>
            <p><strong>Cause:</strong> Hormonal fluctuations (PCOS, puberty, stress)</p>
            <p><strong>Appears:</strong> Jawline, chin, and lower cheeks</p>
            <p><strong>Treatment:</strong> Medical therapy + topical regimen</p>
          </div>
          <div class="type-card featured">
            <div class="popular-badge">Most Common</div>
            <h3>Cystic Acne</h3>
            <p><strong>Cause:</strong> Deep bacterial infection in pores</p>
            <p><strong>Appears:</strong> Painful, inflamed cysts under the skin</p>
            <p><strong>Treatment:</strong> Intralesional therapy + advanced care</p>
          </div>
          <div class="type-card">
            <h3>Comedonal Acne</h3>
            <p><strong>Cause:</strong> Blocked pores from oil and dead skin</p>
            <p><strong>Appears:</strong> Blackheads and whiteheads</p>
