    <section class="faq section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-grid">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>How long does acne treatment take to show results?</h3>
            <p>Most patients see noticeable improvement within 4-6 weeks. Complete clearance typically takes 3-6 months depending on severity. Consistency with the prescribed regimen is key.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Is acne treatment safe for sensitive skin?</h3>
            <p>Yes. Our dermatologists customise every treatment for your skin type. We use gentle, dermatologist-tested products and adjust concentrations to minimise irritation.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Can acne come back after treatment?</h3>
            <p>With a proper maintenance plan and lifestyle adjustments, recurrence can be minimised. We provide a long-term skincare routine to keep your skin clear.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What is the best treatment for acne scars?</h3>
            <p>Depending on the scar type, we recommend microneedling, fractional laser, chemical peels, or PRP therapy. Often a combination approach gives the best results.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Do you treat hormonal acne (PCOS-related)?</h3>
            <p>Yes. We work with both topical and systemic treatments for hormonal acne, including PCOS-related breakouts. A holistic approach addressing both skin and hormonal factors is used.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Is the consultation really free?</h3>
